<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06155030 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06155030 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  AFRICA; ANIMAL; ASSAULT; SOUTH-CAROLINA; CHILD; WOMAN  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  A 250-pound pet lion burst into a mobile home and mauled a 5-year-old girl andher grandmother before the animal's owner arrived and killed it, authoritiessay.;    &quot;You'd expect anything besides a lion coming in your back door,&quot; thechild's father, Tony Holbrooks, said Sunday.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  250-POUND PET LION MAULS GIRL, GRANDMA  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     The girl, Julie Holbrooks, and her grandmother, 50-year-old ShirleyHolbrooks, were both treated at a local hospital Saturday.;    Julie receivedeight stitches to wounds in her throat and chest. Her grandmother's left handwas bandaged where it was punctured by the lion's teeth.;    The lion burstthrough the open back door at 10:30 p.m. Saturday, swept past Holbrooks andpounced on his daughter, family members said.;    &quot;He (the lion) was in thedoor and on top of her,&quot; said the girl's grandmother. &quot;He had his teeth aroundJulie's throat. I put my hand over her neck.&quot;;    Holbrooks wrestled with thelion and hit it over the head with a mop. That broke the handle of the mop andhad little effect on the animal, except to make it angry, he said.;    Thelion and Holbrooks tumbled out the back door of the trailer, where he pickedup a metal bed rail and held the lion at bay until the owner, a neighboridentified as Tony Allen, arrived and shot it.;    The animal was to be testedfor rabies.;    Allen said a padlock on the animal's fence had apparently beenpried off, Wooten said.;    The Holbrooks suspect the animal may have comeinto their home after smelling a ham they had cooked earlier in the day.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Anderson, S.C.  </CITY><EDITION>  Stock Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910603  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Monday  </DAY><MONTH>  June  </MONTH><PG.COL>  3A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  265  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Monday June 3, 199100155030,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>